## Notes

* Changes to <span pulumi-lang-nodejs="`instanceId`" pulumi-lang-dotnet="`InstanceId`" pulumi-lang-go="`instanceId`" pulumi-lang-python="`instance_id`" pulumi-lang-yaml="`instanceId`" pulumi-lang-java="`instanceId`">`instance_id`</span> will force recreation of the resource.
* OAuth2 configuration changes are applied asynchronously and may take some time to complete. The
  resource will poll for job completion using the configured <span pulumi-lang-nodejs="`sleep`" pulumi-lang-dotnet="`Sleep`" pulumi-lang-go="`sleep`" pulumi-lang-python="`sleep`" pulumi-lang-yaml="`sleep`" pulumi-lang-java="`sleep`">`sleep`</span> and <span pulumi-lang-nodejs="`timeout`" pulumi-lang-dotnet="`Timeout`" pulumi-lang-go="`timeout`" pulumi-lang-python="`timeout`" pulumi-lang-yaml="`timeout`" pulumi-lang-java="`timeout`">`timeout`</span> values.
* Only one OAuth2 configuration can exist per instance. Creating a new configuration will replace
  any existing configuration.
* After a configuration has been applied, a restart of RabbitMQ is required for the changes to take effect.

